    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8525" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">στεφανόω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">στέφανος</span>), pass. perf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐστεφάνωται</span>, plup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-το</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">put around as a crown;</span> the pass. is to be understood
          literally, but it may be paraphrased ‘encircles,’ ‘encompasses,’ etc.,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 10.195</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 11.36</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            5.739</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 15.153</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; τά τ᾽ οὐρανὸς ἐστεφάνωται</span>, ‘with
          which the heaven is crowned,’ <i><span class="en">Il.
            18.485</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
